{
  "stem": "4284.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And after 1939, especially with the invasion of Poland, Germany, of course, changed everything because now they started building ghettos and started building concentration camps, which ultimately became extermination camps.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The first concentration camp in Dachau was opened four weeks after Hitler came to power in 1933.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And although the Germans always claimed that they didn't know anything about it, you don't have 13 major, major, major concentration camps all over Germany and know they don't exist.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, when you asked for assistance from any German family-- as I mentioned we lived in an apartment house with Gentile families-- the standard answer is to be, I would love to help you, but I'm afraid I'll catch pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Pneumonia was the catch phrase that the Germans always would send to the surviving family members of those that they have killed, that your dear departed have died of pneumonia in the concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The method of killing didn't mean anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was just the fact, the notification was pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "On the rare occasion, heart failure, but pneumonia was the catch phrase.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the Germans used this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Instead of saying, I'm afraid I'm going to end up in the concentration camp, which they claimed they didn't know anything about-- they did.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Everyone knew it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because any infraction and any criminal activity would end up with a confinement in a concentration camp, with a rare reappearance.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "People just simply would not come back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So pneumonia was the catch phrase.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Consequently, with the original intent to have concentration camps for internment in Germany, now after World War II this philosophy changed, and they started building ghettos.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
